CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService(8) System Manager's Manual CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService(8)

NAME

CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService — service for migrating persisted file bookmark data from a legacy agent to its replacement

DESCRIPTION

CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService is a service used during first login of a user after updating from an older OS build to migrate persisted file bookmarks from a legacy agent to its replacement.

There are no configuration options to CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService, and users should not run CalendarAgentBookmarkMigrationService manually.
